and change values without
obscuring your view.

00:01:02.576 --> 00:01:05.646 A:middle
The Force Touch display
adds a new dimension

00:01:05.836 --> 00:01:07.026 A:middle
to the user interface.

00:01:08.476 --> 00:01:10.996 A:middle
Apple Watch's interface
is attuned

00:01:11.186 --> 00:01:12.596 A:middle
to the wearer's presence.

00:01:13.356 --> 00:01:15.146 A:middle
It wakes when you
raise your wrist

00:01:15.696 --> 00:01:18.086 A:middle
and it sleeps when you lower it.

00:01:18.916 --> 00:01:23.816 A:middle
Apple Watch blurs the boundaries
between software and hardware.

00:01:24.886 --> 00:01:28.936 A:middle
And the Taptic Engine creates
discrete, sophisticated

00:01:29.276 --> 00:01:34.056 A:middle
and nuanced experiences by
engaging more of your senses.

00:01:35.276 --> 00:01:38.566 A:middle
Apple Watch is ideally
suited for quick looks

00:01:38.926 --> 00:01:40.146 A:middle
and fast interactions.

00:01:41.036 --> 00:01:42.306 A:middle
The apps that you design

00:01:42.306 --> 00:01:45.606 A:middle
for Apple Watch should take
advantage of these things.

00:01:47.086 --> 00:01:51.016 A:middle
Your apps should complement
their companion iPhone app

00:01:51.826 --> 00:01:55.106 A:middle
by making information
and actions quicker

00:01:55.186 --> 00:01:57.236 A:middle
and more convenient to access.

00:01:58.436 --> 00:02:02.606 A:middle
Or they should extend the
functionality of your iPhone app



00:01:58.436 --> 00:02:02.606 A:middle
Or they should extend the
functionality of your iPhone app

00:02:02.606 --> 00:02:05.096 A:middle
in ways that were
previously not possible.

00:02:06.646 --> 00:02:11.516 A:middle
Making really great Apple Watch
apps requires a different mind

00:02:11.586 --> 00:02:15.636 A:middle
set and approach than
designing for iOS or for Mac.

00:02:17.186 --> 00:02:20.046 A:middle
Which is why today I
would like to share

00:02:20.046 --> 00:02:24.026 A:middle
with you the three key
foundational design themes

00:02:24.026 --> 00:02:28.826 A:middle
of the Apple Watch, and the
apps that we made to run on it.

00:02:29.376 --> 00:02:32.656 A:middle
The first theme is about
personal communication.

00:02:33.696 --> 00:02:36.046 A:middle
Apple Watch is designed
to be worn.

00:02:36.866 --> 00:02:40.466 A:middle
No other other Apple
device has ever been

00:02:40.466 --> 00:02:43.076 A:middle
so closely connected
to the user.

00:02:44.566 --> 00:02:47.386 A:middle
Interactions on Apple Watch
create a more intimate

00:02:47.826 --> 00:02:50.456 A:middle
and personal experience
with technology.

00:02:51.516 --> 00:02:55.206 A:middle
The communication that occurs
between your app and the people

00:02:55.206 --> 00:02:58.466 A:middle
who use it should be just
as intimate and personal.

00:02:59.856 --> 00:03:02.126 A:middle
Now consider how we
communicate with each other.



00:02:59.856 --> 00:03:02.126 A:middle
Now consider how we
communicate with each other.

00:03:02.126 --> 00:03:05.026 A:middle
When we are speaking with
someone, we try to get a sense

00:03:05.026 --> 00:03:07.306 A:middle
of what the other
person wants to know

00:03:07.406 --> 00:03:09.006 A:middle
and what they are
trying to tell us.

00:03:09.616 --> 00:03:13.336 A:middle
We try to use terms that
they'll understand and concepts

00:03:13.336 --> 00:03:14.216 A:middle
that they are familiar with.

00:03:15.586 --> 00:03:17.946 A:middle
When they look busy or
stressed out, we try to get

00:03:17.946 --> 00:03:19.196 A:middle
to the point more quickly.

00:03:20.026 --> 00:03:22.036 A:middle
Personal communication
requires us

00:03:22.476 --> 00:03:24.726 A:middle
to be attentive and empathetic.

00:03:25.576 --> 00:03:28.976 A:middle
Now, take that and apply it
to the design of your apps.

00:03:30.076 --> 00:03:32.466 A:middle
Probably one of the
most important aspects

00:03:32.536 --> 00:03:36.136 A:middle
of personal communication
is just being considerate

00:03:36.136 --> 00:03:37.606 A:middle
of people's time and attention.

00:03:38.456 --> 00:03:40.006 A:middle
We are all busy people.

00:03:40.136 --> 00:03:42.816 A:middle
We live in a world filled
with constant distraction.

00:03:43.346 --> 00:03:44.426 A:middle
We often don't want

00:03:44.426 --> 00:03:47.826 A:middle
to be disturbed unless it
is something super urgent

00:03:48.156 --> 00:03:50.106 A:middle
or something we care
about deeply.

00:03:50.956 --> 00:03:52.886 A:middle
This is especially
true when it comes

00:03:52.936 --> 00:03:55.036 A:middle
to notifications on Apple Watch.

00:03:55.966 --> 00:03:58.096 A:middle
Apple Watch taps
a person's wrist

00:03:58.096 --> 00:03:59.716 A:middle
when they receive
a notification.



00:04:00.436 --> 00:04:03.476 A:middle
This makes notifications
much more noticeable.

00:04:04.096 --> 00:04:06.656 A:middle
So carefully consider
how frequently you send

00:04:06.656 --> 00:04:07.926 A:middle
notifications to people.

00:04:07.926 --> 00:04:11.726 A:middle
They will get annoyed if you
send notifications too often.

00:04:12.666 --> 00:04:15.776 A:middle
Keep in mind that there's
no way for people to choose

00:04:16.185 --> 00:04:19.916 A:middle
which of your apps notifications
they'll receive on their watch.

00:04:20.546 --> 00:04:22.646 A:middle
They can only choose
whether or not they want

00:04:22.646 --> 00:04:25.886 A:middle
to receive notifications
from your app on their watch.

00:04:27.056 --> 00:04:30.716 A:middle
Avoid pestering them by frequent
interruptions throughout

00:04:30.806 --> 00:04:31.246 A:middle
the day.

00:04:32.066 --> 00:04:33.906 A:middle
Otherwise they will
pretty quickly wind

00:04:33.906 --> 00:04:36.986 A:middle
up turning off notifications
from your app on their watch

00:04:37.526 --> 00:04:39.436 A:middle
and maybe on their
iPhone as well.

00:04:40.706 --> 00:04:42.656 A:middle
Next, keep it relevant.

00:04:43.276 --> 00:04:45.876 A:middle
When we talk with someone,
we try to say things

00:04:45.876 --> 00:04:46.836 A:middle
that the other person is going

00:04:46.836 --> 00:04:48.746 A:middle
to find interesting
or informative.

00:04:49.596 --> 00:04:52.046 A:middle
Similarly the notifications
that you send

00:04:52.046 --> 00:04:55.776 A:middle
to people should contain
valuable and useful information.

00:04:56.576 --> 00:05:00.156 A:middle
People should actually feel
thankful for the notifications



00:04:56.576 --> 00:05:00.156 A:middle
People should actually feel
thankful for the notifications

00:05:00.346 --> 00:05:01.366 A:middle
that you send to them.

00:05:02.196 --> 00:05:04.766 A:middle
Now, determining relevance
can sometimes be pretty

00:05:04.766 --> 00:05:05.556 A:middle
straight forward.

00:05:06.316 --> 00:05:09.236 A:middle
CNN sends notifications
about breaking news stories.

00:05:09.936 --> 00:05:12.366 A:middle
It's a reasonable assumption
on their part that people

00:05:12.366 --> 00:05:14.966 A:middle
who have downloaded their
app and installed it

00:05:14.966 --> 00:05:16.566 A:middle
on their watch want to know

00:05:16.566 --> 00:05:18.966 A:middle
about major news
stories as they unfold.

00:05:19.836 --> 00:05:23.426 A:middle
But for many apps or situations
this approach wouldn't work

00:05:23.426 --> 00:05:23.946 A:middle
so well.

00:05:24.696 --> 00:05:28.476 A:middle
Being relevant often requires
understanding context.

00:05:29.246 --> 00:05:31.706 A:middle
People's interests may
vary based on all sorts

00:05:31.706 --> 00:05:33.136 A:middle
of contextual factors.

00:05:33.786 --> 00:05:35.486 A:middle
By understanding that context,

00:05:35.486 --> 00:05:39.286 A:middle
you can prioritize certain
information or functions.

00:05:40.296 --> 00:05:43.496 A:middle
Now, the two main contextual
factors that are used

00:05:43.496 --> 00:05:46.896 A:middle
to determine relevancy
are location and time.

00:05:48.146 --> 00:05:50.956 A:middle
Let's take a look at how
location can be used.

00:05:52.296 --> 00:05:54.866 A:middle
Invoice2Go is an app
that enables people

00:05:54.866 --> 00:05:57.176 A:middle
to track the hours
that they work

00:05:57.176 --> 00:05:59.246 A:middle
and send invoices
to their clients.

00:05:59.846 --> 00:06:02.176 A:middle
For many of the people
who use their app,



00:05:59.846 --> 00:06:02.176 A:middle
For many of the people
who use their app,

00:06:02.176 --> 00:06:03.956 A:middle
time tracking is
based on location.

00:06:05.336 --> 00:06:08.066 A:middle
Billing starts when they
arrive at the job site,

00:06:08.576 --> 00:06:10.096 A:middle
and it ends when they leave.

00:06:11.036 --> 00:06:14.766 A:middle
Invoice2Go will optionally send
you a notification as a reminder

00:06:15.026 --> 00:06:18.156 A:middle
to start and stop time
tracking based on location.

00:06:18.716 --> 00:06:20.136 A:middle
By using your location,

00:06:20.186 --> 00:06:23.616 A:middle
Invoice2Go makes tracking
billable hours more convenient

00:06:23.996 --> 00:06:25.736 A:middle
and more accurate than trying

00:06:25.736 --> 00:06:29.336 A:middle
to remember how long you worked
hours or even days later.

00:06:30.576 --> 00:06:33.696 A:middle
Now as with location it is
important to find the right time

00:06:33.996 --> 00:06:35.266 A:middle
to communicate with someone.

00:06:35.896 --> 00:06:37.866 A:middle
Some information
is only relevant

00:06:37.866 --> 00:06:39.556 A:middle
at very specific moments.

00:06:40.276 --> 00:06:41.766 A:middle
So, for example, when
you are traveling

00:06:41.766 --> 00:06:44.826 A:middle
with American Airlines, their
app will send a reminder

00:06:44.826 --> 00:06:47.136 A:middle
when it's time for you
to leave for the airport.

00:06:47.706 --> 00:06:49.766 A:middle
This is very relevant
information.

00:06:49.766 --> 00:06:51.336 A:middle
No one wants to miss
their flight.

00:06:52.806 --> 00:06:54.266 A:middle
Now, another big aspect

00:06:54.266 --> 00:06:57.526 A:middle
of personal communication
is just paying attention.

00:06:58.466 --> 00:06:59.746 A:middle
People say this all
the time, right?

00:06:59.746 --> 00:07:02.176 A:middle
It is important for
you to pay attention.



00:06:59.746 --> 00:07:02.176 A:middle
It is important for
you to pay attention.

00:07:02.676 --> 00:07:03.696 A:middle
Well, it is true.

00:07:04.146 --> 00:07:05.166 A:middle
Without paying attention,

00:07:05.166 --> 00:07:07.916 A:middle
you can never really know
what it is that people want.

00:07:08.766 --> 00:07:10.566 A:middle
So, for example, if
you're not sure what kind

00:07:10.566 --> 00:07:13.026 A:middle
of notifications people are
going to find most relevant,

00:07:13.516 --> 00:07:14.796 A:middle
just ask them to tell you.

00:07:15.566 --> 00:07:18.266 A:middle
Nike running and lots of
other apps have settings

00:07:18.266 --> 00:07:19.626 A:middle
to allow people determine

00:07:19.626 --> 00:07:22.266 A:middle
which notifications
they want to receive.

00:07:23.276 --> 00:07:26.916 A:middle
These kinds of settings are
what we might call explicit

00:07:26.916 --> 00:07:28.126 A:middle
user preferences.

00:07:29.026 --> 00:07:32.286 A:middle
They are very direct ways to
determine what is most important

00:07:32.326 --> 00:07:34.026 A:middle
to the people who use your app.

00:07:34.746 --> 00:07:37.496 A:middle
However, people don't
often explore app settings.

00:07:37.916 --> 00:07:39.486 A:middle
They can be difficult to find.

00:07:39.846 --> 00:07:42.986 A:middle
It takes an investment of
time to muck around with them.

00:07:43.016 --> 00:07:44.526 A:middle
People don't always
know what they do.

00:07:45.686 --> 00:07:48.186 A:middle
That's where implicit user
preferences will come in.

00:07:48.976 --> 00:07:50.256 A:middle
When you get to know someone,

00:07:50.256 --> 00:07:52.636 A:middle
you learn about their
tastes and their interests.

00:07:53.186 --> 00:07:55.746 A:middle
A lot of this you pick up just
by observing what it is they

00:07:55.746 --> 00:07:57.666 A:middle
like to talk about and do.

00:07:58.606 --> 00:08:01.296 A:middle
For instance, if you regularly
get coffee with a friend,



00:07:58.606 --> 00:08:01.296 A:middle
For instance, if you regularly
get coffee with a friend,

00:08:01.816 --> 00:08:04.516 A:middle
you probably know what kind
of coffee they like to drink

00:08:04.876 --> 00:08:06.216 A:middle
and how they like it prepared.

00:08:06.726 --> 00:08:09.696 A:middle
Because of that knowledge, you
can go and order them a drink,

00:08:10.306 --> 00:08:12.726 A:middle
and you would get just the
right thing that they wanted

00:08:12.836 --> 00:08:14.676 A:middle
without them having
to even tell you.

00:08:15.536 --> 00:08:18.386 A:middle
By observing and responding
to people's interactions

00:08:18.386 --> 00:08:21.106 A:middle
or behaviors, your
app can make subtle

00:08:21.246 --> 00:08:22.916 A:middle
but significant adjustments

00:08:22.916 --> 00:08:25.526 A:middle
to better accommodate
the preferences

00:08:25.526 --> 00:08:26.726 A:middle
of the people who use it.

00:08:27.686 --> 00:08:30.796 A:middle
The Fitness app is a great
