Perhaps these controls could
be added below and accessed

00:12:30.036 --> 00:12:33.086 A:middle
by scrolling, but with the stop
watch it is really important

00:12:33.086 --> 00:12:37.256 A:middle
that the time stays on screen at
all times in a fixed location.

00:12:38.366 --> 00:12:40.236 A:middle
Now, the menu plays
an instrumental role

00:12:40.236 --> 00:12:43.466 A:middle
in allowing apps like
Weather, Calendar and messages

00:12:43.466 --> 00:12:47.486 A:middle
and many other apps to focus
more on content and information.

00:12:48.816 --> 00:12:51.746 A:middle
Another huge benefit
of Menus is efficiency.

00:12:52.516 --> 00:12:56.026 A:middle
Menus make actions far
quicker for people to access.

00:12:56.736 --> 00:12:59.046 A:middle
For example, the
top level screen

00:12:59.046 --> 00:13:02.046 A:middle
in the messages app contains
a list of conversations.



00:12:59.046 --> 00:13:02.046 A:middle
in the messages app contains
a list of conversations.

00:13:02.776 --> 00:13:04.756 A:middle
The menu for the
screen has an action

00:13:04.756 --> 00:13:06.466 A:middle
to start a new conversation.

00:13:07.106 --> 00:13:09.396 A:middle
Now, if this action
wasn't in the menu,

00:13:09.966 --> 00:13:12.856 A:middle
it would probably be
displayed in line with all

00:13:12.856 --> 00:13:14.016 A:middle
of your conversations.

00:13:14.756 --> 00:13:18.456 A:middle
The trouble is, this could be
a really, really tall screen,

00:13:18.456 --> 00:13:20.886 A:middle
and what you are looking
at could be very far away

00:13:20.886 --> 00:13:22.386 A:middle
from where that action is.

00:13:23.096 --> 00:13:27.306 A:middle
And it would be hard
for people to remember

00:13:27.306 --> 00:13:30.286 A:middle
if that action was all the
way at the top of the screen

00:13:30.736 --> 00:13:33.466 A:middle
or all the way down by
the bottom of the screen.

00:13:34.286 --> 00:13:36.406 A:middle
Menus allow accessing actions

00:13:36.946 --> 00:13:39.626 A:middle
without losing your
current scroll position.

00:13:40.806 --> 00:13:46.966 A:middle
Now, Menus are also a great when
your app has a global control

00:13:46.966 --> 00:13:49.776 A:middle
that you want people to be
able to access from any screen.

00:13:50.256 --> 00:13:53.406 A:middle
So for example, in the
activity app, there's an action

00:13:53.406 --> 00:13:55.136 A:middle
for changing your
daily move goal.

00:13:55.626 --> 00:13:57.576 A:middle
This action is shown
in the menu no matter

00:13:57.686 --> 00:13:58.786 A:middle
where you are in the app.

00:13:59.726 --> 00:14:02.416 A:middle
The activity app is
structured as a page-based app.



00:13:59.726 --> 00:14:02.416 A:middle
The activity app is
structured as a page-based app.

00:14:02.416 --> 00:14:04.456 A:middle
If that control wasn't
in the menu,

00:14:05.186 --> 00:14:07.546 A:middle
it would perhaps
be in its own page.

00:14:07.946 --> 00:14:10.676 A:middle
But that would require four
swipes just to get to it

00:14:10.676 --> 00:14:11.826 A:middle
from the first screen.

00:14:12.486 --> 00:14:13.936 A:middle
By putting this action
in the menu,

00:14:13.936 --> 00:14:15.566 A:middle
you simply press
the screen no matter

00:14:15.566 --> 00:14:17.326 A:middle
where you are and there it is.

00:14:18.156 --> 00:14:21.256 A:middle
Another benefit of menus is
that they can avoid redundancy.

00:14:21.846 --> 00:14:24.116 A:middle
Let's go back to the
activity app for a second.

00:14:24.476 --> 00:14:27.186 A:middle
If we didn't put this
action into a menu

00:14:27.246 --> 00:14:30.496 A:middle
or on its own screen, we
could have multiple instances

00:14:30.596 --> 00:14:32.166 A:middle
of it on every page.

00:14:32.756 --> 00:14:34.276 A:middle
But that would be
pretty redundant.

00:14:34.816 --> 00:14:37.696 A:middle
Plus it could lead people
to be incorrectly assume

00:14:37.966 --> 00:14:41.246 A:middle
that that action had something
specifically to do with the page

00:14:41.246 --> 00:14:42.956 A:middle
that they were currently
looking at.

00:14:43.306 --> 00:14:44.066 A:middle
That would be wrong.

00:14:44.636 --> 00:14:49.606 A:middle
Okay. So I've gotten a lot
of questions about what kinds

00:14:49.606 --> 00:14:51.376 A:middle
of things people
should put into a menu.

00:14:52.256 --> 00:14:54.756 A:middle
Menus are primarily
for contextual actions.

00:14:55.306 --> 00:14:58.056 A:middle
That is actions that are
relevant to the current context.

00:14:58.636 --> 00:15:00.596 A:middle
Context here refers
to two things.



00:14:58.636 --> 00:15:00.596 A:middle
Context here refers
to two things.

00:15:00.596 --> 00:15:03.926 A:middle
It could be the app or it
could be the current screen.

00:15:04.876 --> 00:15:06.996 A:middle
So activity is for
the app as a whole.

00:15:07.826 --> 00:15:10.696 A:middle
But in messages, as we saw
when you are looking at a list

00:15:10.696 --> 00:15:14.186 A:middle
of conversations, you have an
option to add a new message.

00:15:14.676 --> 00:15:15.886 A:middle
So when you are looking

00:15:15.886 --> 00:15:18.576 A:middle
at an individual
conversation, the menu changes.

00:15:19.126 --> 00:15:22.646 A:middle
A different set of actions are
appropriate for this context.

00:15:23.406 --> 00:15:25.116 A:middle
Making sure that the contents

00:15:25.116 --> 00:15:29.716 A:middle
of your menu are contextually
relevant to the app as a whole

00:15:29.716 --> 00:15:31.706 A:middle
or to the current screen
is really important.

00:15:32.346 --> 00:15:36.416 A:middle
People need to know what these
actions are going to act upon.

00:15:37.226 --> 00:15:39.846 A:middle
So in this case, it is clear
that these actions are going

00:15:39.846 --> 00:15:42.596 A:middle
to effect the current
conversation being viewed,

00:15:42.596 --> 00:15:44.966 A:middle
because that was what was
displayed before people pressed

00:15:45.136 --> 00:15:45.676 A:middle
the screen.

00:15:46.976 --> 00:15:49.856 A:middle
Another good use of menus is
for view mode preferences.

00:15:50.576 --> 00:15:54.026 A:middle
That menu with different
stop watch options is a view

00:15:54.026 --> 00:15:55.006 A:middle
mode preference.

00:15:56.046 --> 00:15:57.926 A:middle
Another example is
from the Calendar app.

00:15:58.796 --> 00:16:01.016 A:middle
There is a toggle for
switching between a list view



00:15:58.796 --> 00:16:01.016 A:middle
There is a toggle for
switching between a list view

00:16:01.016 --> 00:16:03.376 A:middle
of your schedule or a
time proportionate view

00:16:03.376 --> 00:16:04.016 A:middle
of your schedule.

00:16:04.886 --> 00:16:07.226 A:middle
View mode preferences
are highly contextual

00:16:07.226 --> 00:16:09.546 A:middle
because they affect
the appearance

00:16:09.546 --> 00:16:10.636 A:middle
of the current screen.

00:16:12.016 --> 00:16:14.596 A:middle
It is worth mentioning
that menus are optional.

00:16:14.596 --> 00:16:17.626 A:middle
There is no need to have
a menu for a given screen

00:16:17.626 --> 00:16:18.636 A:middle
if there's no actions

00:16:18.636 --> 00:16:20.286 A:middle
or preferences that
are appropriate.

00:16:21.036 --> 00:16:22.496 A:middle
And some apps might
be simple enough

00:16:22.496 --> 00:16:24.266 A:middle
that they don't need
a menu at all.

00:16:27.616 --> 00:16:31.866 A:middle
Finally, it is not always
good to put actions in a menu.

00:16:32.456 --> 00:16:36.256 A:middle
Critical path actions, meaning
actions that are necessary

00:16:36.256 --> 00:16:40.166 A:middle
for the user to continue forward
in your app and complete a task,

00:16:40.946 --> 00:16:43.026 A:middle
should not be displayed
in a menu.

00:16:43.126 --> 00:16:44.646 A:middle
They should be presented
in line.

00:16:45.316 --> 00:16:48.746 A:middle
Displaying actions in line
makes them more discoverable.

00:16:49.356 --> 00:16:51.176 A:middle
So, for example,
in the Fitness app

00:16:51.606 --> 00:16:54.506 A:middle
when we've completed a work
out, you are given this choice

00:16:54.506 --> 00:16:56.626 A:middle
to either save or
discard the information

00:16:56.626 --> 00:16:58.056 A:middle
that was recorded
for your work out.

00:16:58.686 --> 00:17:00.456 A:middle
This is not an optional
decision.



00:16:58.686 --> 00:17:00.456 A:middle
This is not an optional
decision.

00:17:00.456 --> 00:17:03.546 A:middle
You need to make the decision
one way or another in order

00:17:03.546 --> 00:17:07.226 A:middle
for you to progress
forward in the app.

00:17:07.226 --> 00:17:09.736 A:middle
In addition, if the
person's highly likely

00:17:09.736 --> 00:17:11.536 A:middle
to select a particular action,

00:17:12.046 --> 00:17:14.736 A:middle
then it should probably also
be shown in a main interface.

00:17:15.526 --> 00:17:18.076 A:middle
For example when you go
to listen to a voicemail

00:17:18.076 --> 00:17:20.626 A:middle
on the phone app, the chances
that you are going to want

00:17:20.626 --> 00:17:24.935 A:middle
to press that play button are
somewhere around 100 percent.

00:17:25.935 --> 00:17:28.296 A:middle
Right? Putting that action

00:17:28.296 --> 00:17:31.036 A:middle
in a menu would make it
needlessly inconvenient

00:17:31.036 --> 00:17:32.386 A:middle
for people to access.

00:17:33.516 --> 00:17:36.246 A:middle
And while calling the person
back who left the message

00:17:36.796 --> 00:17:39.906 A:middle
and deleting the voicemail are
definitely secondary actions,

00:17:40.296 --> 00:17:42.866 A:middle
there's still plenty of
space in this interface

00:17:42.926 --> 00:17:45.536 A:middle
to display those
controls without leading

00:17:45.536 --> 00:17:48.326 A:middle
to usability problems
or visual clutter.

00:17:49.856 --> 00:17:52.776 A:middle
The next aspect of Holistic
Design that I would like to talk

00:17:52.776 --> 00:17:54.486 A:middle
about is the Digital Crown.

00:17:56.016 --> 00:17:59.606 A:middle
The Digital Crown
enables fluid, responsive

00:17:59.706 --> 00:18:01.036 A:middle
and precise scrolling.



00:17:59.706 --> 00:18:01.036 A:middle
and precise scrolling.

00:18:01.796 --> 00:18:05.266 A:middle
So when designing your app,
don't feel like you need

00:18:05.266 --> 00:18:08.636 A:middle
to make everything visible
on screen at one time.

00:18:09.076 --> 00:18:10.256 A:middle
It is just not necessary.

00:18:11.396 --> 00:18:13.856 A:middle
So the detail screen in the
Stocks app, for example,

00:18:13.856 --> 00:18:15.666 A:middle
contains a lot of information.

00:18:16.476 --> 00:18:18.746 A:middle
Since there's no need to show
it all on screen at once,

00:18:18.786 --> 00:18:20.516 A:middle
the most important
information gets

00:18:20.516 --> 00:18:22.746 A:middle
to be displayed above the fold.

00:18:23.216 --> 00:18:24.946 A:middle
It's given a lot
room to breathe,

00:18:24.946 --> 00:18:27.146 A:middle
and we can see the
current values displayed

00:18:27.146 --> 00:18:30.016 A:middle
in much larger text, it's
a nice visual presentation.

00:18:30.906 --> 00:18:32.976 A:middle
The same is true for
apps like Weather

00:18:33.776 --> 00:18:36.266 A:middle
or Activity or many others.

00:18:37.036 --> 00:18:38.946 A:middle
Trying to show everything
on screen

00:18:38.946 --> 00:18:41.516 A:middle
at once is a sure fire recipe

00:18:41.586 --> 00:18:45.276 A:middle
for having a really cramped
looking interface with text

00:18:45.276 --> 00:18:46.506 A:middle
that is too hard to read.

00:18:46.506 --> 00:18:51.716 A:middle
In WatchOS2, the Digital Crown
becomes even more powerful.

00:18:52.546 --> 00:18:54.916 A:middle
There's a new WatchKit
control called the Picker

00:18:54.916 --> 00:18:57.136 A:middle
which I'm sure many of you
have already learned about.

00:18:57.986 --> 00:18:59.986 A:middle
It gives you a lot of
great possibilities

00:18:59.986 --> 00:19:02.096 A:middle
for the design of your app.



00:18:59.986 --> 00:19:02.096 A:middle
for the design of your app.

00:19:02.096 --> 00:19:03.776 A:middle
Pickers come in three
different styles.

00:19:04.016 --> 00:19:05.626 A:middle
This is the stack style Picker.

00:19:05.626 --> 00:19:08.346 A:middle
It provides a way to navigate
and select from a list

00:19:08.346 --> 00:19:09.996 A:middle
of images or a set of images.

00:19:10.636 --> 00:19:12.816 A:middle
There's a list style
Picker which can be used

00:19:12.816 --> 00:19:15.656 A:middle
to select among an array
of text or numeric options,

00:19:16.446 --> 00:19:19.426 A:middle
and the sequence style Picker
which lets you pick an image

00:19:19.426 --> 00:19:21.896 A:middle
out of an image sequence
so you can do something

00:19:21.956 --> 00:19:23.146 A:middle
like this star rating.

00:19:23.716 --> 00:19:26.776 A:middle
And you can also use
a coordinated option

00:19:26.776 --> 00:19:29.846 A:middle
which allows you to display an
image sequence and pick an image

00:19:29.846 --> 00:19:32.966 A:middle
from the sequence to reinforce
the value of the Picker.

00:19:33.526 --> 00:19:36.626 A:middle
For example, when we
change the hour value here,

00:19:37.146 --> 00:19:40.766 A:middle
that orange arc is
being coordinated

00:19:40.766 --> 00:19:43.746 A:middle
and it reinforces the
value of the hour.

00:19:44.276 --> 00:19:47.656 A:middle
Now, the Picker allows values

00:19:47.746 --> 00:19:50.706 A:middle
to be displayed inline
and adjusted inline.

00:19:51.356 --> 00:19:54.566 A:middle
This is important because
it obviates the need

00:19:54.566 --> 00:19:56.536 A:middle
for having a completely
separate interface

00:19:56.536 --> 00:19:57.786 A:middle
for changing a selection.

00:19:58.436 --> 00:20:00.246 A:middle
As a result, it can
make interactions



00:19:58.436 --> 00:20:00.246 A:middle
As a result, it can
make interactions

00:20:00.246 --> 00:20:02.626 A:middle
with your Watch app
far more efficient,

00:20:03.566 --> 00:20:07.936 A:middle
and making selections inline
allows you to retain context.

00:20:08.536 --> 00:20:10.286 A:middle
When we're adjusting
the data value,

00:20:10.286 --> 00:20:12.516 A:middle
it's nice that we can
see what the month

00:20:12.516 --> 00:20:16.046 A:middle
and year is at the same time.

00:20:17.256 --> 00:20:20.516 A:middle
When using a Picker,
there's a few options

00:20:20.516 --> 00:20:21.506 A:middle
that you should be aware of.

00:20:22.176 --> 00:20:24.046 A:middle
First, Pickers have outlines.

00:20:24.386 --> 00:20:26.326 A:middle
Outlines help people
to understand

00:20:26.326 --> 00:20:30.006 A:middle
that a Picker has focus,
meaning people understand

00:20:30.006 --> 00:20:33.836 A:middle
that when they rotate the
Digital Crown, the outline,

00:20:33.836 --> 00:20:36.536 A:middle
the value that is outlined
in green will be adjusted.

00:20:37.106 --> 00:20:39.426 A:middle
This is important when you
have two or more Pickers

00:20:39.426 --> 00:20:41.466 A:middle
that are displayed on
screen at the same time.

00:20:42.046 --> 00:20:45.346 A:middle
In the example of the timer
app, the outlines let us know

00:20:45.346 --> 00:20:47.516 A:middle
that both hour and
minutes can be adjusted

00:20:47.856 --> 00:20:52.506 A:middle
and which one will respond to
rotations of the Digital Crown.

00:20:53.806 --> 00:20:55.556 A:middle
Outlines are not always needed.

00:20:56.056 --> 00:20:58.686 A:middle
So in this example, there
is no need for an outline

00:20:58.686 --> 00:21:00.286 A:middle
because there's only
one Picker on screen.



00:20:58.686 --> 00:21:00.286 A:middle
because there's only
one Picker on screen.

00:21:00.976 --> 00:21:03.866 A:middle
However, if this
screen were to scroll,

00:21:03.866 --> 00:21:06.136 A:middle
an outline would be
needed because people need

00:21:06.136 --> 00:21:08.956 A:middle
to know whether rotating the
Digital Crown will scroll the

00:21:08.956 --> 00:21:10.886 A:middle
screen or adjust
the Picker value.

00:21:12.126 --> 00:21:13.676 A:middle
You can also add a caption

00:21:13.676 --> 00:21:16.576 A:middle
if it's not clear what the
items in your Picker are.

00:21:16.706 --> 00:21:19.466 A:middle
For example, when you
are selecting different

00:21:19.466 --> 00:21:21.466 A:middle
complications, some
of these items aren't

00:21:21.466 --> 00:21:22.956 A:middle
totally self-explanatory.

00:21:23.406 --> 00:21:25.926 A:middle
They require a caption
to explain what they are.

00:21:27.326 --> 00:21:31.186 A:middle
Now, captions are set on a per
item basis, but if every item

00:21:31.486 --> 00:21:33.796 A:middle
in the Picker has the same
caption, it will serve

00:21:33.796 --> 00:21:35.486 A:middle
as a label for the
Picker itself.

00:21:35.856 --> 00:21:39.886 A:middle
Okay. The last setting
that you need to be aware

00:21:39.886 --> 00:21:43.066 A:middle
of is the contextual
indicator or scroll indicator.

00:21:43.396 --> 00:21:45.926 A:middle
It displays when the
Digital Crown is rotated.

00:21:46.486 --> 00:21:48.346 A:middle
The contextual indicator
is useful

00:21:48.346 --> 00:21:51.686 A:middle
for helping people understand
about how many options they have

00:21:51.686 --> 00:21:54.436 A:middle
to choose from and where
they are in that list.

00:21:54.856 --> 00:22:00.226 A:middle
Now, the last aspect of
Holistic Design that I would



